  "text": "where d 1 , d 2 , and d 3 are the individual desirability functions of the three responses, and w 1 , w 2 , and w 3 are the weights assigned for each response. The objective is to maximize the value of D, which will be equal to 1 when all the responses are on target limits (d = 1) and equal to zero if any of the responses is outside the limits (d = 0). Otherwise, the value of the overall desirability will be between zero and one [CITATION_1] .",
